6 Nsys^(-1/2), where Nsys is the number of systems used\nand the range is due to dependence on how many metallic absorption lines in\neach system are compared.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Apr 2010 00:02:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Sep 2010 23:38:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-18"}
